    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Return the canonical path of the specified filename, eliminating any symbolic links encountered in the path (if they are supported by the operating system). On Windows, this function will also resolve MS-DOS (also called 8.3) style names such as C:\\\\PROGRA~1 to C:\\\\Program Files. By default, the path is evaluated up to the first component that does not exist, is a symlink loop, or whose evaluation raises OSError. All such components are appended unchanged to the existing part of the path. Som..."
